transcripts:
No one stands a chance against a real hombre (man), except a guy who knows what hombre means. For a casually bilingual style I recommend el (the) messy look. "First-o" take a fingertip of paste and mix it in your hands. Then rake your hair strongly and spin it muchacho (boy). There you go, not just a pretty hairstyle. I also speak a language and a half. 

Mejor (better)?

Si, tres y medio (Yeah, three and a half).

Mix, rake, spin. Easy for every day
